The paper deals with covert wireless communication, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and security and privacy (cs.CR). It also discusses the impact of network density on covert communication, which falls under networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed countermeasure involves randomized transmission scheduling, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and system and control (cs.SI).
